er Scenarios & Testing]\\n- [ ] CHK010 Is the UAT index content requirement specific to test case IDs and titles only? [Clarity, Spec ¬ßUser Acceptance Tests, Spec ¬ßClarifications]\\n\\n## Requirement Consistency\\n\\n- [ ] CHK011 Are role terms consistent (Referee vs Reviewer) across all sections? [Consistency, Spec ¬ßTerminology, Spec ¬ßSecurity & Privacy Considerations, Spec ¬ßUser Scenarios & Testing]\\n- [ ] CHK012 Do edge cases align with acceptance scenarios for the same UC? [Consistency, Spec ¬ßEdge Cases, Spec ¬ßUser Scenarios & Testing]\\n- [ ] CHK013 Do functional requirements map one-to-one with user stories and UC IDs? [Consistency, Spec ¬ßRequirements, Spec ¬ßUse Case Coverage]\\n- [ ] CHK014 Is public schedule access consistent between UC-03 and UC-29? [Consistency, Spec ¬ßUser Story 3, Spec ¬ßUser Story 29]\\n- [ ] CHK015 Are security/privacy statements consistent with public-access scenarios? [Consistency, Spec ¬ßSecurity & Privacy Considerations, Spec ¬ßUser Stories 1-3, Spec ¬ßUser Story 29]\\n\\n## Acceptance Criteria Quality\\n\\n- [ ] CHK016 Are success criteria measurable and tied to UC/TC coverage? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec ¬ßSuccess Criteria]\\n- [ ] CHK017 Are acceptance scenarios present for every user story? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec ¬ßUser Scenarios & Testing]\\n- [ ] CHK018 Are independent tests traceable to acceptance scenarios for each story? [Acceptance Criteria, Spec ¬ßUser Scenarios & Testing]\\n- [ ] CHK019 Is the UAT pass condition explicitly defined for release readiness? [Measurability, Spec ¬ßSuccess Criteria, Spec ¬ßUser Acceptance Tests]\\n\\n## Scenario Coverage\\n\\n- [ ] CHK020 Are alternate flows from UC extensions captured in acceptance scenarios for each use case? [Coverage, Spec ¬ßUser Scenarios & Testing]\\n- [ ] CHK021 Are exception/error scenarios for authentication, payment declines, and missing data explicitly specified? [Coverage, Spec ¬ßEdge Cases]\\n- [ ] CHK022 Are recovery requirements defined after notification delivery failures? [Gap, Spec ¬ßEdge Cases]\\n- [ ] CHK023 Are save/resume submission scenarios fully specified (state after partial save, resume behavior)? [Coverage, Spec ¬ßUser Story 10]\\n- [ ] CHK024 Are schedule generation/edit/publish flows covered across admin/editor roles without gaps? [Coverage, Spec ¬ßUser Stories 22-25]\\n\\n## Edge Case Coverage\\n\\n- [ ] CHK025 Are zero-state scenarios (no announcements, no assigned papers, no published schedule) defined? [Edge Case, Spec ¬ßEdge Cases]\\n- [ ] CHK026 Are invalid input formats (email, manuscript file) handled with explicit requirements? [Edge Case, Spec ¬ßEdge Cases]\\n- [ ] CHK027 Are concurrency/conflict cases (simultaneous schedule edits, reviewer workload limit) specified? [Gap, Spec ¬ßUser Stories 17, 22, 24]\\n- [ ] CHK028 Are data availability failures (missing scheduling data) specified with outcomes? [Edge Case, Spec ¬ßEdge Cases]\\n\\n## Non-Functional Requirements\\n\\n- [ ] CHK029 Are performance goals tied to specific user journeys rather than generic statements? [Clarity, Plan ¬ßTechnical Context]\\n- [ ] CHK030 Are audit logging requirements explicitly listed for critical actions? [Completeness, Spec ¬ßSecurity & Privacy Considerations]\\n- [ ] CHK031 Are privacy requirements defined beyond classification (e.g., access limits, retention)? [Gap, Spec ¬ßSecurity & Privacy Considerations, Spec ¬ßDependencies]\\n\\n## Dependencies & Assumptions\\n\\n- [ ] CHK032 Are dependencies on UC/TC files documented with ownership or versioning expectations? [Assumption, Spec ¬ßDependencies]\\n- [ ] CHK033 Are external service requirements (payment, notification) defined for availability and failure handling? [Gap, Spec ¬ßUser Stories 11, 12, 25, 27, 28]\\n- [ ] CHK034 Are assumptions about public access and authentication explicitly recorded? [Assumption, Spec ¬ßClarifications, Spec ¬ßAssumptions]\\n\\n## Ambiguities & Conflicts\\n\\n- [ ] CHK035 Are terms like \\\"valid\\\", \\\"complete\\\", and \\\"secure\\\" defined with concrete criteria? [Ambiguity, Spec ¬ßUser Story 5]\\n- [ ] CHK036 Is the overlap between schedule viewing use cases (UC-03 vs UC-29) clearly reconciled? [Ambiguity, Spec ¬ßUser Story 3, Spec ¬ßUser Story 29]\\n\\n## Notes\\n\\n- Check items off as completed: `[x]`\\n- Add comments or findings inline\\n- Link to relevant resources or documentation\\n- Items are numbered sequentially for easy reference\\nEOF\"}","call_id":"call_BBpRNQANuQYUXByDTCLzCUBC"}}
